This paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it proposes an alternative parametrization for Exponential Linear Units (ELUs) that improves learning in deep neural networks. It is also likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it discusses the properties of the ELU activation function and how it can be tuned. Additionally, the paper may belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as ELUs are commonly used in image recognition tasks. It may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as deep learning is a popular technique in AI research. Finally, it may belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as it discusses the mathematical properties of the ELU activation function.
